My husband had the ribeye from the ranch in Warner and was blown away by how good it was and, let me tell you, heâs VERY particular! I had the flatiron steak which was also delicious. We ordered the beef tallow potatoes and brussel sprouts as our sides. My only negative comment would be that the brussel sprouts seemed a bit overdone. They were quite dark in colour (almost black) and a little on the dry side. The potatoes however, were very good. We finished off with the Baked Alaska which we thoroughly enjoyed. All in all we had a wonderful experience and have been telling our friends and family to check out your fine establishment.
